<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861217-0168 </DOCNO><HL> Sensormatic Will DevelopSystem With Allied-Signal</HL><DD> 12/17/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SNSR ALD </IN><DATELINE> BOCA RATON, Fla.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sensormatic Electronics Corp. and Allied-Signal Inc. said they definitively agreed to form a joint venture to develop, make and distribute an anti-theft electronic surveillance system for retail and industrial markets.    The joint venture, Identitech, will be 50%-owned by each company. Identitech will further develop and market a detection system Allied-Signal designed. Sensormatic, a maker and marketer of electronic surveillance equipment, said it will have the exclusive right to market the system to retail and industrial customers. Allied-Signal, based in Morristown, N.J., has interests in aerospace, auto parts, electronics and chemicals. </TEXT></DOC>